                <mxCell id="10" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: pplxSerif, pplxSerif, ui-serif, Georgia, Cambria, &amp;quot;Hiragino Mincho ProN&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Yu Mincho&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Songti SC&amp;quot;, SimSun, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, MingLiU_HKSCS, &amp;quot;Songti TC&amp;quot;, PMingLiU, AppleMyungjo, Batang, serif; background-color: color(srgb 0.0901961 0.0862745 0.0823529);&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: light-dark(rgb(214, 213, 212), rgb(255, 255, 255)); font-size: 13px;&quot;&gt;The MSR partition is a hidden reserved area Windows uses for future partition management, metadata, converting basic and dynamic disks, and internal storage operations, while Linux usually does not need it because its tools manage partitions and filesystems directly&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;" style="text;strokeColor=default;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;spacingLeft=4;spacingRight=4;overflow=hidden;points=[[0,0.5],[1,0.5]];portConstraint=eastwest;rotatable=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;dashed=1;dashPattern=1 4;" vertex="1" parent="9">
